post_text: Registration is now open for the 2020-2021 school year for returning students. Login to Powerschool at https://nwshelby.powerschool.com with your parent login account. On the left side under Navigation you click on the link labeled Returning Student Application. This will begin the registration process. If you have forgotten your powerschool parent account username or password there is a link under the powerschool login that will help you change or obtain those. If you experience problems you can call the Technology Hotline Monday through Friday 8:00 AM to 4:00 PM at 317-480-1298. If your child will be a new student this year please contact the school building they will be attending for information on how to safely register your child. Thank you.

post_text:
2020 FTA Football/ Cheer Fundraiser
Initial order DEADLINE June 23rd

The Spirit Wear and concessions are the only fundraiser that FTA Football has. Your support is greatly appreciated. Purchasing from this fundraiser always helps two school programs, FTA and the TC Green Machine. The Green Machine is run by the TCHS business students. The goal of The Green Machine is to raise money for various programs throughout the school corporation and the community. You can place an order digitally with the link below. However, we are not able to currently take payments online, so you will need to make payments payable to TCHS, and mail to FTA Spirit Wear C/O Mike Brown 4523 N 825 W Boggstown, IN 46110, or get the payment to a football or cheer director.
The orders take a few weeks to come in.

https://www.tcgreenmachine.com/2020-fta-fundraiser

**Don’t forget to get registered for FTA Football/Cheer. DEADLINE is July 1st.**

Join us on Facebook at FTA Football/Cheer.

To the TC Community:

In accordance with direction from the Indiana Department of Education, k-12 campus facilities are to remain closed to all but essential activities minimally through June 30. Continuous education and meal distribution related activities will continue as planned.

Please direct questions to your student’s teacher and building principal as needed. Further information regarding the resumption of campus activities after June 30 will be shared as it is available.

Thank you for your understanding and patience during this time.

Mr. Hoke
Superintendent- NWCSD

In response to the stress COVID-19 has placed on the medical community, IHSAA has announced that any student-athlete with a valid physical form on file for the 2019-2020 season will also be eligible for the entire 2020-2021 sports year WITHOUT a new physical.

If an athlete did not have a valid physical for the 2019-2020 year, they still MUST get a physical to be eligible for the 2020-2021 sports year.

post_text:
Triton Central School Families,
Starting Thursday, April 2, 2020 free breakfasts and lunches will be available on campus to all Triton Central students in need. Drive thru pickup will be available on Thursdays between the hours of 3 and 5 PM. Pickup will be on a first come/first serve basis. For the safety of our workers, we are asking families to stay in their vehicles. We will create a grab and go drive thru service. Students do not need to be present and no ID/paperwork is required to pickup meals. Meals should not be consumed onsite. Please fill out this brief survey so that we may be prepared to serve you efficiently. If someone does not have an internet connection to fill out the form please call 317-835-7461 and leave your name, telephone number, and how many children you have under 18 in your household. Here is the link to the form https://forms.gle/BkEtH57tLqueBrod8

post_text:
In cooperation with the Shelby County Health Department, the Indiana State Department of Health, and the U.S. Center for Disease Control in addressing the spread of COVID-19 (coronavirus) to and through our community, the Northwestern CSD of Shelby County will restrict access to its Triton Central campus buildings to essential personnel only.

This campus closure will take effect on Monday March 16, 2020 at 8 pm and will remain in effect until Monday March 30, 2020. All access to exterior and interior facilities is suspended during this period.

Thank you for your patience, understanding and support.

post_text:
Open Position - School Psychologist
Northwestern Consolidated School District of Shelby County (home of Triton Central Schools) has an opening for a School Psychologist for the 2020-21 school year. Northwestern is conveniently located near Indianapolis and Greenwood off of I-74.
General responsibilities for this position will include administering psychological and educational evaluations with a team of qualified professionals within prescribed timelines. This person will also serve as a resource for Response to Intervention Teams, and assist school personnel and parents in developing a student’s Individualized Education Program following an evaluation.
Good organizational, communication, and collaboration skills are needed. Interested candidates should contact the Director of Special Education, Terri Branson at 317-435-7067 or tbranson@nwshelbyschools.org.
This position will be open until filled.

The 2019-20 FTA Basketball Night will be on Tuesday, Jan. 28th.

All players and coaches in their FTA gear will get into the LTB vs Shelbyville HS game for FREE...all other parents, etc. will need to pay-$5 each.

We will introduce the FTA teams/coaches at 1/2 time of the JV game (game starts at 6 PM)...please meet the HS staff in the corner near the locker room area with 2 minutes left in the 2nd quarter, we will make an announcement...Thanks and Go Tigers!

October 23, 2019 at 11:07 AM ·

Daily Announcements

October 23, 2019

Happy Wednesday

TCMS is hosting “Breakfast for Veterans” on Tuesday, November 12 at 8:00 a.m. Any TCMS student interested in bringing a veteran to breakfast needs to pick up a registration form from Mrs. Harper before school, after school, during passing period or during lunch.

Any students interested in Winter Guard or Indoor Percussion for this upcoming Winter season needs to attend an information meetingTOMORROW night at 7:30 pm in the TCHS Auditorium. This meeting is for students and parents. See Mr. Shepherd or TritonCentralBands.com for more details.

Drama Club will be having a call out meeting for the Spring show TOMORROW MORNING at 7:00 in Mr.Stone’s room.

Tomorrow’s Breakfast Choices: blueberry bash waffles, cereal, BeneFIT bar, Pop-Tart, string cheese, fruit, and milk

Today’s Lunch Choices: roasted turkey w/ gravy, pizza, cheeseburger, chicken rings, strawberry parfait w/ granola, Italian hoagie, veggies, and fruits

Important Back To School Information:

1) Bus Routes are available at https://www.infofinderi.com/ifi/?cid=NCSOSC4B7HXFOZ6 . This link is also on our websites under parent resources.

2) The first student day is Wednesday, July 31st. This is a Wednesday and WILL NOT be a delayed start day. It will be a normal start school day. The first delayed start Wednesday will be on August 7th.

3) NWCSD will be two E-Learning Days for professional development on Friday, August 16th and Monday September 16th. Students will be working from home on those days in the same manner as on eLearning for Inclement Weather Days.

***ATTENTION FTA Friends and Family***

Thanks to all of you that have already registered your child for FTA. Welcome to the new members. Below is a lot of information for future FTA football business. Please spread the word that we are still taking sign ups! Our numbers at the peewee level (K-1st Grade) are pretty low at the moment and there’s still time to sign up.

**FTA Football/Cheer is still taking sign ups**

Due to the inconvenience the weather caused to some during Saturday’s sign ups, we will offer an extension towards the deadline to sign up through mail until Friday, June 21st and avoid the $10 late fee. We are also offering a LAST in person sign up date of Sunday, June 23rd from 12-2 at the FTA concessions.

See below for important football and cheer information and fundraiser information.

Media Announcement
For Immediate Release
May 7, 2019

The Northwestern Consolidated School District of Shelby County, in partnership with local emergency management agencies, will conduct a countywide safety drill on Tuesday, May 28, 2019 at 9 AM. This training scenario will consist of a simulated hazardous material spill response for local and state agencies and a campus building evacuation and reunification for NWCSD personnel.

Please note that during this time, the NWCSD campus will be closed to visitors. Inquiries regarding the countywide safety drill should be addressed to:

Mr. Chris Hoke
Superintendent
NWCSD of Shelby County
(317) 835-7461

May 2, 2019 at 4:39 PM ·

The TCMS book fair is May 6-10 in the media center. Summer is rapidly approaching, and this is an opportunity for students to purchase a book or two to keep their minds active during the break. Profits from the fair help us buy more books for the students to use at school. Hours will be:
Monday 11:10am-2:30pm
Tuesday 7:55am-11:55am
Wednesday 9:15am-1:20pm
Thursday closed
Friday 7:55-1:40
We accept cash, check, or credit card on site at the fair.
This year Scholastic has added e-wallet which allows you to put money in an account for your child to make book fair purchases from. Here is the link for the e-wallet and also the online fair if you are interested:

https://bookfairs.scholastic.com/bookfairs/cptoolkit/homepage.do?method=homepage&url=tritoncentralmiddleschool

Triton Central High School
Alumni and Friends Pep Band

When: Wed, Nov. 21, 5 (or come as soon as you can)
Where: Meet in TCHS band room (enter door TC A5)
Who: Everyone! (TC community, alumni, etc., YOU)
What to bring: Yourself and instrument, music will be provided (if you need an instrument, please contact me ahead of time)
No need to RSVP, just show up and play

Contact: Joey Shepherd, Band Director
JShepherd@NWShelbySchools.org
(317) 835-3000, ext 1216
www.TritonCentralBands.com

Attention All TC Parents: There will be an information meeting about the 2019 Post Prom Party on Sunday Nov 11th at 5:30pm in the TCHS Library. Details about the event and other opportunities will be discussed, so please attend to help support this event!!!!! Post Prom is for any Junior or Senior enrolled at TC but 9th and 10th grade parents are encouraged to attend as well. If you have any questions, please contact Karen O'Neill at karenjoneill6@gmail.com
